  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study varying inlet flow rate and rotational speed was conducted during model development to inform factor prioritisation; results indicated that hemolysis index is most sensitive to rotational speed above 3000 rpm. This screening informed the acceptance criterion (RH < 1) and operating envelope selection but is documented only in the engineering record, not as a formal structured sensitivity analysis node.",
